3.
 Roles and Responsibilities
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
IT Director
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall serve as Incident Commander for all cybersecurity incidents by default,
 as established in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:4.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Incident Response Policy Overview) and governed by the delegation provisions in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Delegation of Authority and Decision Rights).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall serve as the sole authoritative source for strategic and public-facing incident communications under the One Voice Rule defined in Section 6.1.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall authorize all external communications issued under this policy,
 except where the technical coordination carve-out defined in Section 6.7 applies.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall render the breach determination required to initiate the NRS 603A.220 notification process defined in Section 6.5.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall authorize all external partner engagement during an active incident in accordance with Section 6.6.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall authorize all media and public communications in accordance with Section 6.9.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall make law enforcement referral decisions personally and shall not delegate law enforcement referral authority.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall,
 as the designated Local Agency Security Officer (LASO) under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.11"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Data Governance and Classification Policy),
 execute all CJIS Security Policy Section IR-6 Part (b) external notification obligations in accordance with Section 6.4 and the notification windows established in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:4.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Identification and Reporting Procedures).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall,
 as LASO,
 execute CJIS denial notifications routed from 
