:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall maintain the incident response contact directory as a governed Knowledge Base artifact in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.13"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Knowledge Management Policy) and Section 6.12.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall update the incident response contact directory within one (1) business day of any personnel change affecting an IR role assignment.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Incident Commander (when not the IT Director or Assistant IT Director)
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall exercise communication authorization authority within the scope of the IC delegation established in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 and the One Voice Rule defined in Section 6.1.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall ensure internal status updates are issued in accordance with Section 6.3.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall ensure all incident-related communications are documented in the incident work order in accordance with Section 6.11.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall escalate any condition that may constitute a breach of personal information to the IT Director immediately upon identification,
 in accordance with Section 6.5.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
All Information Operations Personnel
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall comply with the One Voice Rule defined in Section 6.1.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall not issue external communications regarding a cybersecurity incident without IC authorization,
 except where the technical coordination carve-out defined in Section 6.7 applies.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall document all incident-related communications in the incident work order within the timeframes established in Section 6.11.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall not speculate in writing or verbally on incident cause,
 attribution,
 scope,
 or data compromise to any audience until authorized by the IC.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
4.
 Compliance and Exceptions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Compliance with this policy is mandatory for all Information Operations personnel involved in or supporting cybersecurity incident response.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Assessment
\series default
:
 Adherence to communication authorization requirements,
 notification timelines,
 documentation obligations,
 legal review routing requirements,
 and contact directory maintenance shall be assessed through the internal audit process defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Internal Audits,
 Self-Assessment,
 and Control Testing) and the annual policy review and maturity scoring process defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.07"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Annual Policy Review and Maturity Scoring).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Enforcement
\series default
:
 Failure to obtain required authorization before issuing external communications,
 failure to execute CJIS or breach notifications within the timelines established in this policy,
 failure to route communications through legal review when required by Section 6.8,
 failure to document communications as required by Section 6.11,
 or failure to maintain the contact directory validation cadence established in Section 6.12,
 without documented justification,
 shall be treated as non-compliance and may result in corrective action in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Policy Implementation,
 Enforcement,
 and Legal Alignment).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Exceptions
\series default
:
 Exceptions to any requirement of this policy shall be documented in writing with a business justification and approved by the IT Director in accordance with the exception framework established in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
,
 within the delegation constraints of 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 No exception shall be granted on an open-ended basis;
 each exception shall specify a defined remediation timeline and any compensating measures in effect during the exception period.
 No exception may suspend or modify the CJIS notification obligations established in Section 6.4 or the NRS 603A.220 notification obligations established in Section 6.5.
 Oral exceptions are not valid.
\end_layout

