\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.3 Internal and Executive Communications
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
\lang english
Internal Status Updates:

\series default
 The IC shall determine the appropriate cadence for internal status updates based on incident severity,
 operational tempo,
 and response activity.
 The IC shall ensure that internal status updates are issued no less frequently than once per twenty-four (24) hour operational period during an active incident.
 The IC may increase the cadence at any time.
 The IC shall ensure that all internal status updates are documented in the incident work order in accordance with Section 6.11.
 The IC shall ensure that status updates include,
 at minimum,
 the current incident status,
 actions completed since the last update,
 actions planned,
 and any changes to severity classification or scope.
\end_layout

